#: ../../../cmds/alias.rst:2
msgid "alias - create a function"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/alias.rst:5
msgid "Synopsis"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/alias.rst:7
msgid ""
"alias\n"
"alias [--save] NAME DEFINITION\n"
"alias [--save] NAME=DEFINITION"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/alias.rst:15
msgid "Description"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/alias.rst:19
msgid ""
"NOTE: This page documents the fish builtin ``alias``. To see the "
"documentation on any non-fish versions, use ``command man alias``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/alias.rst:22
msgid ""
"``alias`` is a simple wrapper for the ``function`` builtin, which creates a "
"function wrapping a command. It has similar syntax to POSIX shell ``alias``. "
"For other uses, it is recommended to define a :doc:`function <function>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/alias.rst:24
msgid ""
"If you want to ease your interactive use, to save typing, consider using an :"
"doc:`abbreviation <abbr>` instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/alias.rst:26
msgid ""
"``fish`` marks functions that have been created by ``alias`` by including "
"the command used to create them in the function description. You can list "
"``alias``-created functions by running ``alias`` without arguments. They "
"must be erased using ``functions -e``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/alias.rst:28
msgid "``NAME`` is the name of the alias"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/alias.rst:29
msgid ""
"``DEFINITION`` is the actual command to execute. ``alias`` automatically "
"appends ``$argv``, so that all parameters used with the alias are passed to "
"the actual command."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/alias.rst:31
msgid ""
"You cannot create an alias to a function with the same name. Note that "
"spaces need to be escaped in the call to ``alias`` just like at the command "
"line, *even inside quoted parts*."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/alias.rst:33
msgid "The following options are available:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/alias.rst:35
msgid "**-h** or **--help**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/alias.rst:36
msgid "Displays help about using this command."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/alias.rst:38
msgid "**-s** or **--save**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/alias.rst:39
msgid ""
"Saves the function created by the alias into your fish configuration "
"directory using :doc:`funcsave <funcsave>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/alias.rst:42
msgid "Example"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/alias.rst:44
msgid ""
"The following code will create ``rmi``, which runs ``rm`` with additional "
"arguments on every invocation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/alias.rst:48
msgid ""
"alias rmi=\"rm -i\"\n"
"\n"
"# This is equivalent to entering the following function:\n"
"function rmi --wraps rm --description 'alias rmi=rm -i'\n"
"    rm -i $argv\n"
"end"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/alias.rst:55
msgid "``alias`` sometimes requires escaping, as you can see here::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/alias.rst:57
msgid ""
"# This needs to have the spaces escaped or \"Chrome.app...\"\n"
"# will be seen as an argument to \"/Applications/Google\":\n"
"alias chrome='/Applications/Google\\ Chrome.app/Contents/MacOS/Google\\ "
"Chrome'"
msgstr ""

